==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toluic
<hw>To*lu"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, one of three metameric acids,
<chform>CH3.C6H4.CO2H</chform>, which are related to toluene and
analogous to benzoic acids. They are white crystalline substances, and
are called respectively <stype>orthotoluic</stype> <it>acid</it>,
<stype>metatoluic</stype> <it>acid</it>, and <stype>paratoluic</stype>
<it>acid.</it></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toluid</ent>⟦br⟧
